# DigiPub × Submit Manager — Architectural Recovery Plan

> **Prepared:** 2026-03-08 · **Status:** Phase 1–3 Complete — Pending Review

---

## 1. System Architecture Analysis

### 1.1 DigiPub Platform (Hostinger)

| Layer | Technology | Key Files |
|-------|-----------|-----------|
| Framework | Next.js 16 (standalone SSR) | [next.config.mjs](../next.config.mjs) |
| API Server | Hono v4.12 (8 routers) | [app.ts](../src/server/app.ts) |
| ORM | Prisma 7.2 + MariaDB adapter | [config.ts](../lib/db/config.ts) |
| Auth | JWT (jose) + OTP verification | [auth.ts](../lib/db/auth.ts), [middleware.ts](../middleware.ts) |
| Frontend | React 19, TanStack Query, Radix UI | [package.json](../package.json) |
| Database | MySQL/MariaDB — 9 Prisma models | [schema.prisma](../prisma/schema.prisma) |
| Entry Point | Custom [server.js](../server.js) with DB init | [server.js](../server.js) |

```mermaid
graph TB
    subgraph DigiPub["DigiPub — Hostinger"]
        NX["Next.js 16 SSR"]
        HONO["Hono API /api/*"]
        PRISMA["Prisma ORM"]
        DDB[("DigiPub MySQL DB")]
        MW["JWT Middleware"]
    end

    subgraph OJS["Submit Manager — SiteGround"]
        OJSAPP["OJS 3.4+ PHP/Smarty"]
        OJSDB[("OJS MySQL DB<br/>dbkgvcunttgs97")]
    end

    Browser -->|HTTPS| NX
    NX --> MW --> HONO
    HONO --> PRISMA --> DDB
    HONO -->|Direct MySQL| OJSDB
    OJSAPP --> OJSDB
    
    style DDB fill:#1e3a5f,stroke:#38bdf8,color:#e2e8f0
    style OJSDB fill:#14532d,stroke:#4ade80,color:#e2e8f0
```

### 1.2 Submit Manager / OJS Platform (SiteGround)

- **Application:** Open Journal Systems (OJS) 3.4+
- **Runtime:** PHP 8.2.30, MySQL 8.4.5
- **Template engine:** Smarty
- **Database:** 80+ tables following OJS EAV-style patterns (`*_settings` tables)
- **API bridge:** A [debug.php](../submit_manger_api/debug.php) script exists at `submit_manger_api/` that queries OJS DB and renders diagnostics

### 1.3 Integration Points

| # | Integration Point | Mechanism | Direction |
|---|-------------------|-----------|-----------|
| 1 | Journal listing on homepage | Direct MySQL query to OJS DB | OJS → DigiPub |
| 2 | Platform statistics | Direct MySQL query to OJS DB | OJS → DigiPub |
| 3 | OJS health check | MySQL ping to OJS DB | OJS → DigiPub |
| 4 | Batch data sync | Cron script ([ojs-sync-cron.ts](../scripts/ojs-sync-cron.ts)) | OJS → DigiPub |
| 5 | Journal thumbnail images | HTTP URL construction to SiteGround | OJS → DigiPub |
| 6 | PHP debug/diagnostic | [debug.php](../submit_manger_api/debug.php) on SiteGround | Standalone |

### 1.4 Data Flow

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    participant Browser
    participant NextJS as DigiPub (Next.js)
    participant HonoAPI as Hono API
    participant DigiDB as DigiPub DB
    participant OjsDB as OJS DB (SiteGround)

    Browser->>NextJS: GET /journals
    NextJS->>HonoAPI: /api/ojs/journals
    HonoAPI->>HonoAPI: Check in-memory cache (5min TTL)
    alt Cache miss
        HonoAPI->>OjsDb: Direct MySQL query (mysql2)
        OjsDb-->>HonoAPI: Raw journal rows
        HonoAPI->>HonoAPI: Map + Zod validate
        HonoAPI->>HonoAPI: Cache response
    end
    HonoAPI-->>NextJS: JSON response
    NextJS-->>Browser: Rendered page

    Note over HonoAPI,DigiDB: Admin CRUD uses Prisma → DigiPub DB
    Note over HonoAPI,OjsDb: OJS reads use mysql2 → OJS DB
```

